1
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:25,170


2
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:39,000
   
 Cheon Yeon Soo, what do you think love is? 

3
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:42,767
 Listening and obeying well? 

4
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:45,067
 No. 

5
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:47,267
 Giving up your sugar stars? 

6
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,633
 No. 

7
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:54,333
 Then… wanting to see someone every day? 

8
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:56,800
 That's not it either. 

9
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,733
 Then what is it? 

10
00:00:58,733 --> 00:01:00,767
 Love is... 

11
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:04,567
 being by each other's side. 

12
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:11,133
 Like this? 

13
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:16,033
 Yeah, and giving a tight hug. 

14
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:21,567
 Holding hands is okay, too. 

15
00:01:21,567 --> 00:01:24,100
 - Really? 
 - Yeah. 

16
00:01:24,867 --> 00:01:26,367
   

17
00:01:26,367 --> 00:01:29,433
 Oh dear, dumb bear. 

18
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:34,733
 I said I hate it. Give me a different one!  

19
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:36,800
 What's wrong with being number 3? 

20
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,600
 Why am I number 3? 

21
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:41,033
 We won the stick-hopping game because of me. 

22
00:01:41,033 --> 00:01:44,000
 I'm stronger than Han Woo and Seung Eon. 

23
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,833
 Gosh, dumb bear! 

24
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:48,360
 We are a family, the Kang Hee family.  

25
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:50,700
 Do you think the numbers are random? 

26
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:53,900
 Seung Eon has been with us since he was 7, so he is number 1. 

27
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:56,833
 Han Woo has been playing with us since he was 8, so he is number 2. 

28
00:01:56,833 --> 00:02:00,567
 And you moved here when you were 9. 

29
00:02:01,867 --> 00:02:04,333
 Then, what do I have to do to become number 1? 

30
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:08,233
 I really want to be your number 1. 

31
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:10,667
 Well? I don't know. 

32
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,433
 Hey! 

33
00:02:44,933 --> 00:02:47,367
The words "I love you"...

34
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:52,000
are said when people are leaving.

35
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:55,500
Yeon Soo,

36
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:00,800
what I am trying to say…

37
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,533
Don't do it.

38
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:06,233
Don't do it, please!

39
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:08,267
I love you.

40
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:15,100
I love you, Yeon Soo.

41
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:52,770
♫  I realized it as I stared quietly into your eyes  ♫

42
00:03:52,770 --> 00:04:00,550
♫  My love for you, fearlessly, keeps growing   ♫

43
00:04:00,550 --> 00:04:07,530
♫  My confession that never reached you, I love you  ♫

44
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:16,860
♫  Will a part of my sincerity reach you today?  ♫

45
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:20,633
You said love is about hugging...

46
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:23,933
and holding hands.

47
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:27,667
We knew that when we were 10. Why don't we know that now?

48
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:29,967
Don't do this, Yeon Soo.

49
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:34,567
We can't go back to before the accident.

50
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:38,433
No, it doesn't matter.

51
00:04:39,367 --> 00:04:41,333
Can't we just think about the two of us?

52
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:44,733
If you say it doesn't matter, will my sin disappear?

53
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:49,033
If you say you love me, if you hug me and hold my hand,

54
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:50,900
will what happened disappear?

55
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:55,367
Will my dead mother, your dead father come back to life?

56
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:01,167
Don't make it more painful, Yeon Soo.

57
00:05:04,767 --> 00:05:08,600
Fine, do as you like.

58
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,667
But just know this,

59
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:13,633
no matter how much you try to avoid and hide,

60
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:16,733
nothing will change.

61
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:20,267
You will come back again,

62
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:25,333
because I'll be right here.

63
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:29,020
♫  I love you  ♫

64
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:32,850
♫  My confession to you  ♫

65
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:39,530
♫  Feels more precious than yesterday  ♫

66
00:05:39,530 --> 00:05:44,220
♫  My shy, hesitant first words to you  ♫

67
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:54,860
♫  Those seemingly meaningless words contained my feelings for you  ♫

68
00:05:54,860 --> 00:06:02,900
♫  I may not have said "I love you"  ♫

69
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:09,720
♫  But it was all love  ♫

70
00:06:10,810 --> 00:06:13,540
♫  Look, I'm doing it again  ♫

71
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:18,420
♫  I'm still shaking  ♫

72
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:25,200
♫  Will you hold my hand and hold me close?  ♫

73
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:29,850
♫  It took me longer than everyone else  ♫

74
00:06:29,850 --> 00:06:33,540
♫  But I was the most sincere  ♫

75
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:40,440
♫  Every day that passed took me a lot of courage  ♫

76
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:51,940
♫  I might be late in saying "I love you"  ♫

77
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:00,200
   

78
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:06,267
What's the matter?

79
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,500
Yeon Soo.

80
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:28,433
   

81
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:58,500
   

82
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:01,033
   

83
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:35,233
Ms. Kang Hee.

84
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:53,300
I took care of the registration in advance, since we're hospital mates.

85
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:58,167
See, I told you I could come alone.

86
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:03,833
- Yes. 
 - Goodbye.

87
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,767
- Patient Ji Chun Pil. 
 - Yes.

88
00:10:05,767 --> 00:10:09,167
Stay here, it's all right.

89
00:10:22,220 --> 00:10:25,640
   

90
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:28,600
The results are not good.

91
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:31,367
Has it relapsed?

92
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:33,100
Is he your guardian?

93
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,533
Yes, I'm his son.

94
00:10:34,533 --> 00:10:37,867
Let's get you admitted first.

95
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,467
Will we have to do chemotherapy again?

96
00:10:41,467 --> 00:10:46,767
Yes, besides chemotherapy, there are no other options.

97
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:53,370
   

98
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,567
Here it is.

99
00:10:58,367 --> 00:11:01,067
- Yes, it's all done. 
 - Thank you.

100
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,300
   

101
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:23,100
 The customer's phone is turned off, please leave a message… 

102
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,367
Have you tried giving a confession?

103
00:11:45,167 --> 00:11:50,667
In the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

104
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:54,533
God illuminates our hearts.

105
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:56,733
Firmly believing in God's mercy,

106
00:11:56,733 --> 00:12:01,700
confess truthfully the sins you have committed.

107
00:12:04,233 --> 00:12:09,300
My heart is stronger than that of most priests.

108
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:12,900
I'll listen to any confession...

109
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:15,567
and keep your secrets.

110
00:12:16,133 --> 00:12:18,233
Does God...

111
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:22,600
forgive any sin if it's confessed?

112
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:26,033
Does He forgive anything?

113
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:27,867
Of course.

114
00:12:34,967 --> 00:12:37,967
I killed someone.

115
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:42,800
I killed my mom and Yeon Soo's dad,

116
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:48,367
and then I forgot about it for 20 years.

117
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:56,600
Then I dared to love Yeon Soo.

118
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,633
Can I be forgiven, too?

119
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:07,233
Can He forgive someone like me?

120
00:13:28,267 --> 00:13:30,600
Do you know how to turn yourself in?

121
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,233
I did some research.

122
00:13:32,233 --> 00:13:34,400
This is all that comes up?

123
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:41,700
- Open it. 
 - How are you planning to turn yourself in?

124
00:13:42,233 --> 00:13:43,700
Do you have any evidence?

125
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:47,567
The doll that you supposedly shoved in, it's gone now. Right?

126
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:49,560
What about the car?

127
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:51,633
It has already been scrapped, and it's gone. Right?

128
00:13:51,633 --> 00:13:53,767
How old were you back then?

129
00:13:53,767 --> 00:13:55,467
You were young.

130
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:58,000
You found that memory after 20 years,

131
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:01,000
how can you be sure it's true or not?

132
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:07,800
You just want to punish yourself.

133
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:12,933
You didn't even talk to Yeon Soo, you just cut ties and ran away. Right?

134
00:14:12,933 --> 00:14:16,467
Shouldn't Yeon Soo be the one giving the punishment, if there is any?

135
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:19,600
Whether you apologize or get punished,

136
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:23,667
shouldn't you at least talk to Yeon Soo first?

137
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:37,133
   

138
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:48,733
Mr. Yeon Soo.

139
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:56,833
Chun Pil was diagnosed with leukemia 3 years ago.

140
00:14:57,367 --> 00:15:00,433
He had 12 rounds of chemotherapy back then.

141
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:02,233
I had no idea, not at all.

142
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:06,067
I also had cancer surgery back then.

143
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,067
 - Mr. Tarzan? 
 - Ms. Hepburn? 

144
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:22,300
 - Hello. 
 - Oh, yes. 

145
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:25,900
Did you hear that we met at a classic film gathering?

146
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:27,567
 Here… 

147
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:34,300
 The hospital life alone was a bit scary and lonely. 

148
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,900
 Meeting Mr. Tarzan has been a great help. 

149
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:41,667
 I also matched outfits with Ms. Hepburn like this. 

150
00:15:41,667 --> 00:15:47,533
 This kind of walk makes it bearable. 

151
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:53,100
 Let's be hospital friends. 

152
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:57,267
 Until each of us has a guardian, 

153
00:15:57,267 --> 00:15:59,567
 let's come to the hospital together. 

154
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:06,067
 Let's end the hospital life altogether. 

155
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,290
 Once I finish this round of chemotherapy, 

156
00:16:09,290 --> 00:16:13,500
 I don't plan on coming back anymore. 

157
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:17,367
I thought he was just saying that back then,

158
00:16:18,267 --> 00:16:20,862
but it seemed he was serious.

159
00:16:20,862 --> 00:16:23,628
He said he won't receive any more treatment.

160
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,200
I can't persuade him.

161
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:32,200
So, Mr. Yeon Soo, please try to talk to him.

162
00:16:32,733 --> 00:16:36,067
Where is he now?

163
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:45,300
Anyway, the night view here is really…

164
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:48,067
The night view is really beautiful.

165
00:16:48,067 --> 00:16:53,833
I was planning to spend this Christmas here with you.

166
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:02,600
Yeon Soo, Merry Christmas.

167
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,233
Oh, Merry Christmas in advance.

168
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:06,233
Merry Christmas in advance, sir.

169
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,700
Enough.

170
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:12,733
- I've made up my mind, Yeon Soo. 
 - About what?

171
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:15,567
I need to change my car.

172
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:18,567
- I'm going to change it to a camper. 
 - All of a sudden?

173
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:24,110
Driving around wherever my feet take me, to places with no name...

174
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,633
and suddenly disappear without a trace.

175
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:31,400
Then to prevent that, I must follow you around.

176
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:35,933
But there's just one thing that bothers me.

177
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:42,667
I'm worried about Kang Hee and Seung Eon.

178
00:17:42,667 --> 00:17:47,467
Well, you said you'd take responsibility for Kang Hee.

179
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:49,267
What about me?

180
00:17:51,233 --> 00:17:55,100
To me, you are like a father.

181
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:57,433
Why exclude me?

182
00:17:57,433 --> 00:17:59,500
You're not worried about me?

183
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:03,433
Sir,

184
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:07,300
can you please do the chemotherapy?

185
00:18:08,233 --> 00:18:10,333
Or at least,

186
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:14,567
just get admitted.

187
00:18:14,567 --> 00:18:17,267
Hospital gowns don't suit me.

188
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:19,367
What doesn't suit you?

189
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:24,333
If you walk down the hospital corridor wearing a hospital gown, it's like a runway.

190
00:18:25,133 --> 00:18:29,267
That's because you're my fan.

191
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:35,067
It's not because I'm your fan, it's because I'm your son.

192
00:18:36,467 --> 00:18:41,567
Do you know how many memories you and I have together?

193
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:49,133
I once told you that you looked cool playing the guitar.

194
00:18:50,933 --> 00:18:53,633
Then you taught me how to play the guitar.

195
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:59,333
Because I was chubby,

196
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:06,733
when I told you that my friends wouldn't play sports with me,

197
00:19:08,933 --> 00:19:11,033
you played soccer and basketball with me.

198
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:13,933
You talk too much, brat.

199
00:19:17,105 --> 00:19:20,072
Until you say you'll get treated,

200
00:19:21,367 --> 00:19:24,400
just know that I won't give up on you.

201
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:37,600
Chemotherapy makes all your hair fall out.

202
00:19:38,633 --> 00:19:44,000
I spent so much effort regrowing my hair.

203
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:51,467
Let's not tell Kang Hee.

204
00:19:53,867 --> 00:19:58,133
I haven't done much for her until now.

205
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:02,567
Finally,

206
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:07,533
she's able to smile and go about her life.

207
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:10,300
I don't want to make it hard for her.

208
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:14,233
 Kang Hee is not living happily. 

209
00:20:14,233 --> 00:20:16,500
 She is struggling right now. 

210
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:21,133
 So you have to hold on, sir. Please. 

211
00:20:21,133 --> 00:20:23,300
Instead of Kang Hee,

212
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:27,767
I'll take care of you.

213
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:36,333
I don't want you to struggle, either.

214
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:40,000
It's not hard for me.

215
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:36,933
 No matter how much you try to avoid or hide, 

216
00:21:36,933 --> 00:21:39,367
 nothing will change. 

217
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:45,700
 You'll come back again... 

218
00:21:47,067 --> 00:21:49,567
 because I'll be right here. 

219
00:21:54,767 --> 00:21:57,267
I'm sorry, Yeon Soo.

220
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,800
I'm sorry.

221
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:13,833
   

222
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:22,767
Good morning.

223
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:26,733
Where is Yeon Soo?

224
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:28,500
Probably went out?

225
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:33,600
Did he come in last night?

226
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:37,100
Probably?

227
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:39,867
Mr. Kwon, you're neglecting your duties.

228
00:22:39,867 --> 00:22:42,433
No way…

229
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:49,100
Kang Hee.

230
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:55,100
- Where's Yeon Soo? 
 - Weren't you staying together in Seoul?

231
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:59,667
He said he had to go somewhere for a few days due to work.

232
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:06,733
I think it's probably that he's going for interviews.

233
00:23:06,733 --> 00:23:07,833
What interviews?

234
00:23:07,833 --> 00:23:11,500
He's been searching for veterinary researcher jobs.

235
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:17,233
I thought he talked this over with you.

236
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:24,120
   

237
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:40,840
   

238
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:19,967
Ms. Yoon,

239
00:24:20,733 --> 00:24:22,400
are you there?

240
00:24:24,067 --> 00:24:25,733
Are you not there?

241
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,567
It's me, Nan Woo.

242
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,900
It seems she's not here.

243
00:24:55,867 --> 00:24:59,433
I can't face Han Woo anymore.

244
00:25:00,233 --> 00:25:04,433
I shouldn't have interfered when you told me not to.

245
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,900
I'm embarrassed.

246
00:25:08,967 --> 00:25:12,767
Why? Didn't Han Woo thank you that day?

247
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:16,833
- Really? 
 - I would be grateful, too.

248
00:25:16,833 --> 00:25:20,267
You worried about me, ran to me, and caught me.

249
00:25:23,233 --> 00:25:27,100
I'm glad you think that way.

250
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:35,733
Have you sorted all...

251
00:25:36,733 --> 00:25:38,800
your feelings for Yeon Soo?

252
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:41,433
Why should I sort them out?

253
00:25:41,433 --> 00:25:43,500
I can't sort them out.

254
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:49,167
To me, the director

255
00:25:49,167 --> 00:25:52,800
is like… an idol star?

256
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:56,000
He was, he is, and will always be

257
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:59,633
someone I respect and support.

258
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:01,167
Yes.

259
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:05,933
Then, what about Han Woo?

260
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:11,667
Do you like Han Woo?

261
00:26:11,667 --> 00:26:13,467
Then…

262
00:26:15,967 --> 00:26:17,467
That's not right, is it?

263
00:26:17,467 --> 00:26:18,667
Why not?

264
00:26:18,667 --> 00:26:20,333
Is it okay?

265
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:22,767
I don't know.

