325
00:31:05,633 --> 00:31:09,100
Later. Let's talk later.

326
00:31:09,100 --> 00:31:17,700
♫  I'll be your ocean and embrace your tender heart   ♫

327
00:31:28,867 --> 00:31:31,200
Why are you back so soon?

328
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:33,867
You probably find it uncomfortable to see me.

329
00:31:33,867 --> 00:31:36,000
I was a coward.

330
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:40,700
I wanted to believe Yeon Soo's words that it didn't matter.

331
00:31:40,700 --> 00:31:44,167
Listening to your advice to overcome it alongside Yeon Soo,

332
00:31:44,633 --> 00:31:46,667
I wanted to be deceived.

333
00:31:49,333 --> 00:31:53,133
You said Esther is going to the US soon?

334
00:32:16,300 --> 00:32:19,200
Does it taste good when you eat alone?

335
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:22,000
I ordered something that tastes good even when eaten alone.

336
00:32:24,333 --> 00:32:26,267
Is this sauce the secret?

337
00:32:26,267 --> 00:32:28,367
It's addictive.

338
00:32:30,100 --> 00:32:32,000
More than Kang Hee?

339
00:32:33,667 --> 00:32:37,300
Kang Hee is going overseas to study with Esther.

340
00:32:38,500 --> 00:32:42,567
I think that's a good idea too, and I plan to help.

341
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:50,367
Where are you going?

342
00:32:50,933 --> 00:32:52,567
I need to stop them.

343
00:32:52,567 --> 00:32:57,233
Do you think someone like her will feel better running away abroad?

344
00:32:58,033 --> 00:33:02,200
You can't let her live her entire life with guilt, criticizing herself.

345
00:33:02,867 --> 00:33:07,700
I'm going to tell her not to run away, to face it by my side.

346
00:33:07,700 --> 00:33:10,900
As much as Kang Hee is struggling, no, even more so,

347
00:33:10,900 --> 00:33:14,600
I am ready to bear it with her, and endure it all.

348
00:33:38,633 --> 00:33:40,233
Study abroad?

349
00:33:41,633 --> 00:33:43,567
All of a sudden?

350
00:33:46,467 --> 00:33:48,433
Don't even dream about it.

351
00:33:58,433 --> 00:33:59,333
Min Goo.

352
00:33:59,333 --> 00:34:02,600
Hey, no, go back.

353
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:06,200
If you want to register your marriage, you need to go to the town office. Why come to me?

354
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:10,100
Actually, if I want to see a traffic accident investigation record, what should I do?

355
00:34:10,100 --> 00:34:12,100
Traffic accident?

356
00:34:12,100 --> 00:34:13,900
What? What kind? Which one?

357
00:34:13,900 --> 00:34:17,033
You know, our parents' traffic accident long ago.

358
00:34:17,033 --> 00:34:20,000
I want to know the exact details of the accident.

359
00:34:21,567 --> 00:34:23,467
I have the right to know.

360
00:34:23,467 --> 00:34:26,133
Yes, of course you do.

361
00:34:26,133 --> 00:34:28,100
Hold on a second.

362
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:30,967
First, you need to file a viewing request.

363
00:34:30,967 --> 00:34:34,467
You can't do it right now, you need to fill out the application.

364
00:34:34,467 --> 00:34:37,200
- Want help? 
 - Please.

365
00:34:37,200 --> 00:34:38,867
Wait a moment.

366
00:34:55,933 --> 00:34:57,633
Kang Hee,

367
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:04,100
I can't leave you alone in vague guilt.

368
00:35:05,433 --> 00:35:09,233
If my father really ended up like that because of you,

369
00:35:10,867 --> 00:35:14,067
you should take care of me in place of my father.

370
00:35:14,067 --> 00:35:17,133
You should hold me and cheer me up.

371
00:35:18,067 --> 00:35:20,367
Where were you trying to run away to?

372
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:26,933
Nothing is certain yet.

373
00:35:28,767 --> 00:35:31,733
No matter what the conclusion is, stay by my side.

374
00:35:36,067 --> 00:35:38,733
Hold my hand and let's overcome it together.

375
00:35:44,733 --> 00:35:46,700
You're cold, right?

376
00:35:55,233 --> 00:35:57,533
Are you okay?

377
00:35:57,533 --> 00:36:00,400
Sure, I'm okay.

378
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:18,067
Just a moment.

379
00:36:30,533 --> 00:36:33,567
   

380
00:36:37,500 --> 00:36:40,700
Was this why you couldn't be reached?

381
00:36:40,700 --> 00:36:43,667
Why is this still here?

382
00:36:43,667 --> 00:36:45,767
Be honest with me.

383
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:53,467
Well, it's like…

384
00:36:53,467 --> 00:36:55,067
Are you hurt?

385
00:36:55,067 --> 00:36:57,967
Were you hospitalized? Is it a terminal illness?

386
00:36:57,967 --> 00:36:59,300
Not me, but someone else.

387
00:36:59,300 --> 00:37:00,900
Someone else, who?

388
00:37:00,900 --> 00:37:04,967
Well… I went to a conference in Seoul.

389
00:37:04,967 --> 00:37:09,700
A friend was kicked by a horse and broke his ribs.

390
00:37:09,700 --> 00:37:12,933
But I broke some of my own ribs back in the day.

391
00:37:12,933 --> 00:37:15,867
So I gave him advice and just took care of him, as I was there…

392
00:37:15,867 --> 00:37:19,767
You… You're really a terrible liar.

393
00:37:19,767 --> 00:37:22,267
It's not a lie.

394
00:37:24,133 --> 00:37:26,233
I said I'm okay.

395
00:37:27,167 --> 00:37:30,033
Being a large animal vet is a dangerous job.

396
00:37:30,033 --> 00:37:32,533
You be careful, too.

397
00:37:32,533 --> 00:37:33,967
Don't worry.

398
00:37:33,967 --> 00:37:36,100
I'm the top-ranked among the cows in this town.

399
00:37:36,100 --> 00:37:40,567
Were you thinking of getting a job elsewhere because you're number one?

400
00:37:40,567 --> 00:37:44,067
I know you went for an interview, not a conference.

401
00:37:45,133 --> 00:37:46,300
Oh.

402
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:48,967
We hid it from each other to avoid worrying.

403
00:37:48,967 --> 00:37:51,967
Pushing each other away, thinking it's for the other's sake.

404
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:54,967
Let's avoid that.

405
00:37:57,467 --> 00:37:58,967
Okay?

406
00:37:58,967 --> 00:38:00,767
Okay.

407
00:38:00,767 --> 00:38:02,800
Promise?

408
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,400
Promise.

409
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:30,500
Director.

410
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:32,933
Why did you come out? I told you to rest.

411
00:38:32,933 --> 00:38:35,940
You said you don't like the hotel breakfast and have plans for dinner,

412
00:38:35,940 --> 00:38:37,200
so I had to come.

413
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:38,833
I was a bit busy.

414
00:38:38,833 --> 00:38:40,200
Are you dating?

415
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:43,467
Ah, well… it's similar.

416
00:38:44,833 --> 00:38:48,667
Well, please find a replacement for me.

417
00:38:48,667 --> 00:38:51,833
- Have you made up your mind? 
 - I'm trying to make a new start.

418
00:38:51,833 --> 00:38:54,133
I don't want to be under my parents' interference here.

419
00:38:54,133 --> 00:38:56,800
I hate hearing this and that even more.

420
00:38:56,800 --> 00:38:58,600
Anyway,

421
00:38:59,300 --> 00:39:02,400
I think I need to go to the US.

422
00:39:02,900 --> 00:39:04,600
No way.

423
00:39:12,367 --> 00:39:14,933
Walk carefully, it's dangerous.

424
00:39:14,933 --> 00:39:17,967
Why are you acting like this all of a sudden?

425
00:39:17,967 --> 00:39:21,167
Going abroad? Are you sure you won't think about Little Heart?

426
00:39:21,167 --> 00:39:23,833
Can you live as if you forgot everything and nothing happened?

427
00:39:23,833 --> 00:39:26,433
While you're missing Little Heart,

428
00:39:26,433 --> 00:39:28,100
I don't want you to live a life full of regret.

429
00:39:28,100 --> 00:39:30,300
Then what should I do?

430
00:39:30,300 --> 00:39:33,433
Should I raise a fatherless child in Korea?

431
00:39:33,433 --> 00:39:35,433
We can make it happen.

432
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:38,833
Esther, look at yourself properly.

433
00:39:38,833 --> 00:39:40,833
With your beauty, intelligence, and wealth,

434
00:39:40,833 --> 00:39:44,067
overflowing with charm, can't you find a father for the baby?

435
00:39:44,067 --> 00:39:47,467
The only thing you're lacking is a good eye for men.

436
00:39:48,100 --> 00:39:50,867
I'll help you with that, let's find a father together.

437
00:39:50,867 --> 00:39:52,367
What are you talking about?

438
00:39:52,367 --> 00:39:53,900
Hey, are you really crazy?

439
00:39:53,900 --> 00:39:58,100
You should make a new start, but do it with Little Heart.

440
00:39:58,133 --> 00:40:01,400
It's Victor, that rat, who did wrong. Why are you giving up on Little Heart?

441
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:03,133
You haven't done anything wrong.

442
00:40:03,133 --> 00:40:05,567
Be confident, like Esther.

443
00:40:05,567 --> 00:40:08,867
Find a man who will accept you as you are.

444
00:40:10,333 --> 00:40:13,367
- Will there be one? 
 - There will be a line.

445
00:40:13,367 --> 00:40:15,067
Trust me.

446
00:40:25,100 --> 00:40:28,400
If you look inside, it has detailed information about the accident.

447
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:31,467
If there's something you don't know, don't hesitate to ask me.

448
00:40:32,700 --> 00:40:33,833
Thank you, Min Goo.

449
00:40:33,833 --> 00:40:36,867
For what? Take care of Kang Hee.

450
00:40:36,867 --> 00:40:38,367
I'm leaving.

451
00:41:14,900 --> 00:41:17,367
   

452
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:27,600
   

453
00:41:29,333 --> 00:41:32,800
   

454
00:41:45,167 --> 00:41:48,267
 Four cars that slipped on icy roads. 
   

455
00:41:48,267 --> 00:41:50,900
 It was a fatal accident caused by a chain collision. 

456
00:41:50,900 --> 00:41:52,100
   

457
00:41:52,100 --> 00:41:56,533
   
 The overturned car is your father's car. 

458
00:42:29,931 --> 00:42:31,664
Let's go.

459
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:40,500
Really?

460
00:42:40,500 --> 00:42:42,000
He is tall and handsome.

461
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:44,633
That's really something.

462
00:42:44,633 --> 00:42:47,333
I hope he comes soon.

463
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:51,967
Oh? Yeon Soo.

464
00:42:51,967 --> 00:42:53,600
Oh my god!

465
00:42:55,633 --> 00:42:59,767
This is a family meeting place, why are you here?

466
00:42:59,767 --> 00:43:02,500
Kang Hee is my family now.

467
00:43:02,500 --> 00:43:04,833
I won't let go of her hand.

468
00:43:05,767 --> 00:43:08,567
Do you really have to make me look like a bad person?

469
00:43:08,567 --> 00:43:11,900
Just don't act like the bad person, Su Ji.

470
00:43:11,900 --> 00:43:14,567
Just stay quiet for a moment.

471
00:43:14,567 --> 00:43:17,300
You know I clearly don't like her.

472
00:43:17,300 --> 00:43:21,033
Holding hands? What are you thinking?

473
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:24,967
I'm sorry.

474
00:43:24,967 --> 00:43:28,633
I have something important to say.

475
00:43:28,633 --> 00:43:30,767
I'll say it and leave.

476
00:43:30,767 --> 00:43:32,967
Let go of Yeon Soo's hand and talk.

477
00:43:32,967 --> 00:43:36,400
- I'll just… 
 - Su Ji!

478
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:38,867
You really shouldn't be doing this.

479
00:43:42,167 --> 00:43:44,167
Su Ji,

480
00:43:44,167 --> 00:43:46,867
what's with that face?

481
00:43:46,867 --> 00:43:50,900
A flower being angry and frowning?

482
00:43:50,900 --> 00:43:53,600
A flower should smile brightly.

483
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:57,767
That's a right and a responsibility.

484
00:43:57,767 --> 00:44:00,833
So a flower can't be angry?

485
00:44:00,833 --> 00:44:03,767
If there's something to be angry about, I'll be angry myself.

486
00:44:03,767 --> 00:44:07,400
So, solve it through talking

487
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:09,733
and soften your face.

488
00:44:10,633 --> 00:44:14,633
Through conversation, gently.

489
00:44:16,100 --> 00:44:18,167
Okay.

490
00:44:18,167 --> 00:44:20,367
Let's resolve everything here.

491
00:44:20,367 --> 00:44:23,900
Yes, go ahead.

492
00:44:26,067 --> 00:44:30,633
I was really struggling,

493
00:44:31,446 --> 00:44:33,346
you know?

494
00:44:34,100 --> 00:44:36,958
Your dad died suddenly in an accident,

495
00:44:36,958 --> 00:44:40,128
people were gossiping so much.

496
00:44:40,128 --> 00:44:43,767
Besides the accident your dad had,

497
00:44:43,767 --> 00:44:47,333
he was cheating, deceiving me.

498
00:44:49,404 --> 00:44:51,267
Let's leave that out.

499
00:44:51,267 --> 00:44:55,600
It was so tough, I thought of just dying.

500
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:57,533
- What? 
 - Oh my!

501
00:44:57,533 --> 00:45:01,933
Since I was going to die, like "Thelma &amp; Louise".

502
00:45:01,933 --> 00:45:04,412
You know, "Thelma &amp; Louise"?

503
00:45:04,412 --> 00:45:05,600
I know.

504
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:08,233
Let's hit it hard.

505
00:45:08,233 --> 00:45:12,333
Let's go to the cliff and end it in style.

506
00:45:12,994 --> 00:45:18,227
Didn't even make it to the cliff, the car broke down in the middle of nowhere.

507
00:45:19,100 --> 00:45:22,200
Thank goodness! It was heaven's help, Su Ji.

508
00:45:22,200 --> 00:45:24,533
Just listen.

509
00:45:25,267 --> 00:45:29,611
Kang Hee, you! It was because of you!

510
00:45:29,611 --> 00:45:33,077
Kang Hee, your teddy bear!

511
00:45:34,616 --> 00:45:37,982
It was blocking the exhaust pipe.

512
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:42,140
No wonder I felt nauseous,

513
00:45:42,140 --> 00:45:44,360
and I almost threw up while driving.

514
00:45:45,333 --> 00:45:47,500
Mom,

515
00:45:47,500 --> 00:45:49,633
is what you just said true?

516
00:45:49,633 --> 00:45:52,067
It's the truth!

517
00:45:52,067 --> 00:45:54,803
How could a child do that?

518
00:45:54,803 --> 00:45:56,425
Kang Hee, you…

519
00:45:56,425 --> 00:45:59,033
Just because I talked badly about your mom,

520
00:45:59,033 --> 00:46:01,776
is that how you take revenge? On an adult?

521
00:46:01,776 --> 00:46:05,567
I'm still too scared to drive.

522
00:46:05,567 --> 00:46:08,833
Oh, my! Gods! Thank you!

523
00:46:08,833 --> 00:46:11,333
You saved Su Ji's life.

524
00:46:11,333 --> 00:46:15,733
It's all thanks to you that I met Su Ji today.

525
00:46:15,733 --> 00:46:18,367
What? What is…

526
00:46:22,067 --> 00:46:24,600
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

527
00:46:25,167 --> 00:46:27,633
I was wrong.

528
00:46:27,633 --> 00:46:29,500
Please forgive me.

529
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:31,350
You were young,

530
00:46:31,350 --> 00:46:34,960
why go this far…

531
00:46:37,300 --> 00:46:40,033
Thank you so much, Mom.

532
00:46:40,033 --> 00:46:41,733
- Thank you. 
 - No.

