00:51:11,300 --> 00:51:12,733
Did you hear us?

586
00:51:12,733 --> 00:51:14,900
Earlier, I…

587
00:51:14,900 --> 00:51:18,867
I heard it from the restaurant.

588
00:51:20,133 --> 00:51:23,167
Just like you,

589
00:51:23,167 --> 00:51:26,500
I miss Chil Ddaeng.

590
00:51:28,100 --> 00:51:30,867
I understand how you feel.

591
00:51:30,867 --> 00:51:34,300
I also pondered with the same feeling.

592
00:51:35,700 --> 00:51:37,133
That's right.

593
00:51:37,133 --> 00:51:41,933
Even lab dogs have their fate predetermined.

594
00:51:42,967 --> 00:51:47,367
Whenever that happens, Director always says,

595
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:51,333
"Even if they are destined to die tomorrow,

596
00:51:51,333 --> 00:51:57,033
we should make sure they live comfortably today."

597
00:51:57,033 --> 00:51:59,533
While at your farm,

598
00:51:59,533 --> 00:52:04,567
Chil Ddaeng was surely happy.

599
00:52:09,567 --> 00:52:11,400
Thank you, Ms. Nan Woo.

600
00:52:11,400 --> 00:52:14,800
That's really comforting.

601
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:19,300
Well, then, will you buy me food?

602
00:52:19,300 --> 00:52:21,000
Yes.

603
00:52:22,367 --> 00:52:26,600
I left my meal and even my friend to follow you.

604
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:29,167
Oh, of course, I should treat you. Let's go.

605
00:52:29,167 --> 00:52:30,600
Yes.

606
00:52:31,233 --> 00:52:34,600
Is there anything specific you'd like to eat?

607
00:52:34,600 --> 00:52:38,067
Um, anything but beef.

608
00:52:38,067 --> 00:52:39,967
Oh, anything but beef?

609
00:52:39,967 --> 00:52:42,500
Um, then…

610
00:52:47,800 --> 00:52:50,000
Mr. Chun Pil is here.

611
00:52:51,767 --> 00:52:54,967
You should rest, it's late.

612
00:52:54,967 --> 00:52:57,800
I have something to say to Mr. Chun Pil.

613
00:53:23,133 --> 00:53:26,533
Mr. Chun Pil, you're here.

614
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:30,233
Hey, there.

615
00:53:32,867 --> 00:53:34,833
I have a favor to ask.

616
00:53:35,467 --> 00:53:39,433
Thank you for asking.

617
00:53:41,733 --> 00:53:44,567
I'd really like you to listen.

618
00:53:44,567 --> 00:53:46,100
Yeah.

619
00:53:47,267 --> 00:53:51,933
Please, adopt Seung Eon.

620
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:56,167
Seung Eon is my brother.

621
00:53:56,167 --> 00:53:58,367
He's not an orphan.

622
00:53:58,367 --> 00:54:01,800
Thank you for saying that.

623
00:54:02,733 --> 00:54:07,600
It's something I've always kept to myself as well.

624
00:54:08,567 --> 00:54:10,633
I found it...

625
00:54:12,933 --> 00:54:15,767
hard to say to you.

626
00:54:16,867 --> 00:54:19,867
It's not a difficult favor, right?

627
00:54:19,867 --> 00:54:22,800
You just need to go to the town office and apply.

628
00:54:22,800 --> 00:54:24,433
It's that simple?

629
00:54:24,433 --> 00:54:27,000
It's not like you're changing his surname or anything.

630
00:54:27,000 --> 00:54:29,400
Just register with the family department.

631
00:54:29,400 --> 00:54:33,933
If it's that easy, we should have done it earlier.

632
00:54:35,367 --> 00:54:37,333
I feel sorry.

633
00:54:37,333 --> 00:54:41,033
I'm feeling sleepy because I took some medicine.

634
00:54:41,900 --> 00:54:45,500
But I still need to say this.

635
00:54:45,500 --> 00:54:47,700
If I die,

636
00:54:47,700 --> 00:54:52,200
you'll have to split the inheritance with Seung Eon, is that okay?

637
00:54:52,200 --> 00:54:54,900
That won't do.

638
00:54:54,900 --> 00:54:59,567
You should spend all your money and then die.

639
00:54:59,567 --> 00:55:02,533
So live a long, long life.

640
00:55:02,533 --> 00:55:04,600
I got it.

641
00:55:05,500 --> 00:55:06,600
Are you leaving?

642
00:55:06,600 --> 00:55:09,267
The floor is hard.

643
00:55:20,200 --> 00:55:22,500
What is this?

644
00:55:22,500 --> 00:55:24,800
It's medicine, what else?

645
00:55:24,800 --> 00:55:25,867
What kind of medicine?

646
00:55:25,867 --> 00:55:30,133
When you get older, everything starts to hurt.

647
00:55:31,033 --> 00:55:34,800
I got them all at once because it's a hassle.

648
00:55:52,500 --> 00:55:55,700
Yeon Soo, come out.

649
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:01,800
Uh?

650
00:56:05,667 --> 00:56:10,367
Have you ever heard that Mr. Chun Pil is sick?

651
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:14,067
No, I haven't heard anything.

652
00:56:14,067 --> 00:56:19,033
Well, in his room there are bags full of medicine.

653
00:56:19,033 --> 00:56:20,633
It's like one's daily bread.

654
00:56:20,633 --> 00:56:22,333
Really?

655
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:29,467
It's not a fatal illness, right?

656
00:56:29,467 --> 00:56:31,333
Mr. Chun Pil?

657
00:56:32,267 --> 00:56:34,867
Go in and rest quickly.

658
00:56:34,867 --> 00:56:36,600
Good night.

