01:02:23,000 --> 01:02:25,733
Because gods can't die.

730
01:02:25,733 --> 01:02:30,133
That's why death is alluring.

731
01:02:34,100 --> 01:02:36,000
Are you dying?

732
01:02:36,000 --> 01:02:38,467
No, it's just that… Hey, won't you die?

733
01:02:38,467 --> 01:02:39,467
Jeez!

734
01:02:39,467 --> 01:02:42,033
No, everyone dies eventually.

735
01:02:42,033 --> 01:02:44,700
Life has meaning because of death. Right?

736
01:02:44,700 --> 01:02:49,833
It's alluring, even romantic, exactly.

737
01:02:49,833 --> 01:02:52,600
Romantic Mr. Chun Pil,

738
01:02:53,300 --> 01:02:55,500
what's the diagnosis?

739
01:03:15,900 --> 01:03:17,767
Cancer.

740
01:03:33,967 --> 01:03:36,200
Kang Hee.

741
01:03:36,200 --> 01:03:37,600
Kang Hee, I'll explain everything.

742
01:03:37,600 --> 01:03:39,533
- Wait, let me talk… 
 - Don't say a word.

743
01:03:39,533 --> 01:03:41,100
You knew everything.

744
01:03:41,100 --> 01:03:44,233
What Chun Pil's illness is and what that medicine is.

745
01:03:44,233 --> 01:03:46,967
You both went to the hospital together. Right?

746
01:03:48,233 --> 01:03:50,900
That receipt was Chun Pil's, wasn't it?

747
01:03:50,900 --> 01:03:54,133
You kept it from me and checked out a nursing home together?

748
01:03:54,133 --> 01:03:55,600
What on earth were you two thinking?

749
01:03:55,600 --> 01:03:59,933
Am I really nothing? Not even a daughter?

